Phantasmist of CoFE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/20/01 8:15:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They said give up your Epic.</span><hr size=1> Let me give a little perspective on the evolution of Epic Weapons in Vision - I think this might increase the understanding of the role epics play in a guild of numerous sizes.<br>
<br>
When epics first came out, there were three categories of epics for Vision.  Those we had the power to do (like Shaman), those we had the power to do, but NEVER saw a spawn for (Wizard), and those we probably didn't have the power for (Necro).<br>
<br>
If you'll recall, early on, a number of the drops came from Cazic and Innoruuk themselves.  The necro epic took one from each.  It was, for example, out of reach of Vision (at the time).<br>
<br>
Fast forward to a quick look at Vision epics basicly show that everyone who wants one, isn't new, doesn't have a significant bottleneck (Warriors), or isn't a part-time player has one.  (Sure, we have people without - they're either in a large class where they're waiting their turn - PATIENTLY, or their epic simply isn't obtainable by us in large quantities.)<br>
<br>
All-in-all, about half of our &quot;regular&quot; players have epic weapons.<br>
<br>
We have players in Vision now that probably won't get an epic in the forseeable future because of the bottleneck and competition for rare spawns (Warrior, and to a lesser extent Enchanter).  ...and while I'd understand if they left Vision for a quicker mobalizing guild, or one going to VP regularly for green scales, I'd still be hurt deep down inside.<br>
<br>
I had to chant over and over again - stop worring about your epic weapons.  In time they'll come.  Those people who stayed and were patient have their epic weapons (if they took time to prepare for them, and actually wanted 'em).<br>
<br>
So, I say to all of you.  Good things come to those who wait. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
Guildleader: <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=benielsongweaver>Beniel Songweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/20/01 9:00:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They said give up your Epic.</span><hr size=1> I think Palimax misses the whole picture.  Not only was I not allowed to have assistance, but was submitted to badgering to level up for the guild.  This is not about whether or not someone would give me my epic.  I don't want it given.  This is about people not respecting my wishes for my characters development and attempting to dangle incentive to do otherwise than what I wish to do with my character, in my face.  All the while, I am expected to support them in their characters development.  Good of the guild, bullshit.  Good of the guild leader(s) is more like it.  Since when has pimping out the uber characters in the guild at the expense of the not so uber characters been for the good of the guild.  Since when has denying people support based on level requirements been for the good of the guild.  Never.  Shammy epic and a few others are relatively easy compared to War, SK, Cleric, Necro, Bard.   The druid epic is laughably easy.  One uber mob in the whole list.  I assisted 2 times on VSR, both times we had less that 12 people there.  Compared to the minimum of 18 to do any CH aoe casting mob, VSR is a pussy. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=benielsongweaver>Beniel Songweaver</A> at: 12/20/01 9:47:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax S