matter of mind" ~ "If you want him - come and claim him!"<br></STRONG></FONT></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uglencannon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glencannon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/21/01 2:05:26 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They said give up your Epic.</span><hr size=1> Well Beniel, very few our your ex-guild reads these boards so I'll just post my opinion.  Note I am not an officer or anything, this is just my opinion.  I'm sure I'm going to regret this, but I kinda have to comment :-)<br>
<br>
1. Vallis didn't tell you to give up on your epic - we simply said that we couldn't help you kill Vox and we're not strong enough to kill Gore yet.<br>
<br>
2. Vallis didn't badger you to level up - but on the other hand we occasionally have some raids that are 55+ only.  I don't think you were right to complain about this.  If you want to attend all raids, you will need to level up - your choice.<br>
<br>
3. Vallis never said that epics go only to 55+, however most large epic raids are either for (a) high levels who have given long time service to the guild, or (b) lower levels who are just one or two steps away.  You do not fit either category.<br>
<br>
4. ToV armour usually goes to 55+ people for a reason.  Those people regularly show up to Hate/Fear raids to help lower levels farm planes armour, diamonds/BDs for resist gear, etc.  They do so without much expectation of loot since they usually have planes armour already or better.  They show up to help the lower levels get good armour - it is simply common courtesy for the lower levels to help the higher levels upgrade their armour in ToV.<br>
<br>
Like I said before, I totally support your decision to stay 52 and lead Vox raids... but Vallis can't help you and I can't help you since I'm 55 and most of Vallis are over 52.  If you had been patient and collected all those other pieces you need, we might be strong enough to kill Gore by the time you needed the scale.<br>
<br>
I was sorry to see you leave Beniel because you are a good bard and we could sure use your strength.  But I think you were putting your epic before the good of the guild, and that's not right.<br>
<br>
